name: typescript-console-resume
description: Objectives -Create a project folder linked to github, and inside that folder an index.html file and a javascript file. Link the JavaScript file to the index.html file. -Your "resume" will simply be a series of console.log statements to print the resume data to the console. -When you open index.html in the browser, it will be a blank page. That's okay. Your resume will be in the console. (command + option + I, or F12) -Your resume should display the following information:     - Your name     - Your career/field     - A short description of yourself     - A list of your interests     - A list of your past positions that includes company/place name, title, short description of what you did     - A list of your skills -You can make up information if you'd like -In your skill list, skills that are "cool" should begin with BAM:
